com.thomsonreuters.upa.codec

Interface Enum


  • public interface Enum
    Represents an enumeration type, defined as an unsigned two-byte value. Many times, this enumeration value is cross-referenced with an enumeration dictionary (e.g., enumtype.def) or a well-known enumeration definition (e.g., those contained in RDM package). This type allows a value ranging from 0 to 65,535.
